One day, society at large may move beyond the faux drama and shallow scope of “reality” television, to embrace the magnificent and awe-inspiring truth of existence, its beauty, its depth, and the complex and nuanced stories of the unique individuals and characters of earth. Until then, we have American Ninja Warrior…

😂 all jokes asides and with love to all the ninja warrior folk, in 2011, 2012, and 2013, I was a contestant on the show.

While I find the production and execution of ANW and similar contests to lack authenticity and substance, it was great fun, and the underlying premise still holds promise.

A few weeks ago I have the privilege of joining @rafekelley and several friends from the @evolvemoveplay community on a canyoneering expedition and visit to the incredible @sunrayshire. 

It’s was a brilliantly challenging and rewarding to face the slippery, exposed, unforgiving, stinging, cold, exhausting, fun, and magnificently beautiful descent down canyon with these courageous adventurers. The kind of thing that it not easily survived, that you wouldn’t want to do again anytime soon, but that you’re immensely glad you did. Big thanks to Rafe for giving us the opportunity to experience natures raw power and wonder like never before. 

The Shire was otherworldly and inspiring to say the least. The vision, dedication, and magic of that land is something to behold and I’m honored to be among those who have payed a visit. Again thanks to Rafe and his family for sharing what genuinely feels something like the mythical realm of middle earth. 

Special thanks to @travisgrantlee as well for pulling this together with Rafe and getting me out there. And to the whole crew for an exciting and memorable weekend! 

#washington #northwest #rain #trees #canyoneering #sunray #shire #evolvemoveplay #rafekelley #damnson

Couple of clips from a quick solo session — pole slides are hot in PK right now so it was fun to revisit this technique after some limited play with it in the past. These slides are fun, easy, low impact, and play to mental battle more than the physical. All good things for what I’m looking for currently, but that’s not my favorite part about them.

Even though the case for parkour being practical in emergencies is kind of weak and played out, the pk nerd in me recognizes that this technique is truly powerful for the parkour purist. Street lighting is ubiquitous in urban environments and if you can enter these slides from large gaps like we are starting to see with @joescandrett and the like, pole slides can be a serious upgrade to accessing or exiting the all kinds of new territory. As with any parkour technique, it’s scary to think of how far you can really take this. Anyways…I’m old enough to be the president now and this is what I do in my free time 😂

#poleslide #parkour #hangtime #thesqueeze #solosession #denver #thoughts
